&#xa0;
[normal]Written evidence submitted by Richard Browning [OLS0041][bold]&#xa0;
[normal]As a simple Christian
[normal], a believer on the Lord Jesus Christ, I submit this short piece to the Committee
[normal] in a father’s and grandfather’s concern
[normal] for the oncoming generations.
[normal]1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Essentially the young mind is inquisitive and constructive.  This is witnessed not only in the human race but also in the animal creation;  it is quite delightful to observe the tentat
[normal]ive, halting attempts of the young hind or calf, rising to its feet, falling, stumbling, straining, tottering, until finally it leaves the ground and takes a few unsteady steps.  With a child, development is very progressive; physically the watchful parent
[normal]s keep an eye open for anything
[normal] 
[normal]that may hinder or stunt
[normal] its growth, and is continually on the alert for danger, harm, unforeseen hazards.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]This watchful care should be a lesson to us and should always mark the parent/child relationship. The child reaching 
[normal]maturity and finally having the privilege of caring for its parent would never forget the natural ties which
[normal] existed
[normal]; the experience always with the elder yet the strength in the younger.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I have little experience of the internet and of technology generall
[normal]y, but I regret the declining influence of a simple godly way of life, whilst acknowledging much good has arrived with the electronic age.  I was always taught that the best way to distract a child and to save it from danger is to offer something else to d
[normal]raw its attention whilst removing the danger – such as a knife – at the same time.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The lack of respect for the nuclear family with its core of love and devotion
[normal] 
[normal]between committed parents has resulted in fragmented and unequal households with little
[normal] to attr
[normal]act and satisfy, and in undisciplined children.  Government is partly responsible for this in its enactment of laws contrary to teaching in the Holy Scriptures.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]It is incumbent on parents to be aware of where their children are as far as possible and not t
[normal]o neglect them selfishly.  No home should contain 
[normal]“ no
[normal] go “ areas where access is prevented and where harmful activities, literature and material can be hidden.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]It is of course possible to obtain reputable computer security technology, to install it on all
[normal] equipment in the household, to keep it up to date and to maintain firewalls and intrusion detection software.  With virtually every household having internet access there is no easy fix.  Much help can be obtained from websites such as “
[normal] The Big 6 Online 
[normal]Issues “.   Doubtless there are other sources.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]7
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Vigilance is required at all times in the protection of our families.  Concerned parents will never surrender principles to expediency and for their own comfort turn a blind eye.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Read the Book of Job chapter 3
[normal]9, verses 14 to 16 …..  “ the ostrich which leaveth her eggs in the earth, and warmeth them in dust.  And forgetteth that the foot may 
[normal]crush them, or that the wild beast may break them.  She is hardened against her young ones, as though they were not hers;
[normal] her labour is in vain without fear. “
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]9
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]May I respectfully request the Committee should be inspired by the teachings of Holy Scripture in the consideration of the inquiry;
[normal] I am grateful for the opportunity to address it.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]September 2013
